{"key":"post-16387633","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16387633</id>\n<content>Stamets says four to five air exchanges hourly, but that's just to give a rough idea.&amp;nbsp; Four to five air exchanges per hour with one 1/2 pint substrate is a lot different than four to five air exchanges with 20.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There's nothing stealthy about an air pump buzzing under a dresser.&amp;nbsp; That attracts far more attention than a shotgun terrarium in the middle of the room.&amp;nbsp; Have some oyster mushrooms mixed in, since they're faster than cubes to colonize and fruit, and they grow fine on &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;brf cakes&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp; The best place to hide a grow is right out in the open.&amp;nbsp; If someone asks, pick off a couple of oysters and fry them up in some butter.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-007/139225721-pf_oysters_010a.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-007/139225721-thumb_pf_oysters_010a.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-007/139225730-pf_oysters_011a.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-007/139225730-thumb_pf_oysters_011a.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16388431</next>\n<prev>16387598</prev>\n<first>16387539</first>\n<last>17418701</last>\n<when>1339818288</when>\n<utime>06/16/12 06:44 AM</utime>\n</post>"}